nodes.title: CLIP Text Encode (Negative Prompt)

widgets_values:
Analyze the image and evaluate these criteria consecutively:

PRIMARY CONDITION (2):
- Any form of physical interaction between person and object, including:
  • Direct contact (holding/touching/carrying/wearing/using)
  • Body-part contact (kicking/leaning on/sitting on)
  • Object attached to person (bag/accessory/clothing)

SECONDARY CONDITION (2):
- Co-occurrence with clear contextual relationship:
  • Object within arm's reach (on table/floor next to person)
  • Object in active use zone (tools near workstation)
  • Thematically related items (book near reading person)

NEGATIVE CONDITION (1):
- No human present
- Object isolated in separate area
- Purely background objects with no person association

Response rules:

Only output "2" if either Primary or Secondary is met

Only output "1" if all Negative conditions apply

Absolutely no explanations, labels, or text beyond the single character 1/2
